[src:bootstrap-css/css-framework] A **CSS framework** is a software library allowing for easier, more standards-compliant web design using Cascading Style Sheets.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-framework] Most of these frameworks contain at least a grid.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-framework] More functional frameworks also come with more features and additional JavaScript based functions, but are mostly design oriented and focused around interactive UI patterns.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-framework] This detail differentiates CSS frameworks from other JavaScript frameworks.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-framework] Two notable and widely used examples are Bootstrap and Foundation.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-framework] Bigger frameworks use a CSS interpreter such as Less or Sass.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-grid-layout] The **CSS grid layout** module excels at dividing a page into major regions or defining the relationship in terms of size, position, and layering between parts of a control built from HTML primitives.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-grid-layout] Like tables, grid layout enables an author to align elements into columns and rows.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-grid-layout] However, many more layouts are either possible or easier with CSS grid than they were with tables.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-grid-layout] For example, a grid container's child elements could position themselves so they actually overlap and layer, similar to CSS positioned elements.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-grid-layout] The example shows a three-column track grid with new rows created at a minimum of 100 pixels and a maximum of auto.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-grid-layout] Items have been placed onto the grid using line-based placement.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-grid-layout] This sample animation uses `display`, `grid-template-columns`, `grid-template-rows`, and `gap` to create the grid, and `grid-column` and `grid-row` to position items within in the grid.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-grid-layout] To view and edit the HTML and CSS used, click the 'Play' at the top right of the example.
[src:bootstrap-css/css-grid-layout] An overview of the various features provided in the CSS grid layout module.
